JOHANNESBURG - Legendary athlete Zola Budd Pieterse is coming home. The barefoot runner plans to run two marathons in South Africa this year. In 1984 Budd first came to the attention of the world when, at 17-years-old, she broke the women’s 5 000m world record. READ: Zola Budd's tribute to Pierre Korkie She'll be taking on the Two Oceans and the Comrades in memory of her brother, who committed suicide last year. Budd said she loved being back in South Africa.